      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility"> ¶ Hamburg,15 ¶  ¶ June ¶  ¶ 1854 ¶ Most ¶  ¶ esteemed ¶  ¶ Sir, ¶  ¶ I am sending you herewith the manuscript of the Mueller plants worked on by Professor Meisner for the ¶  ¶ Linnaea ¶ . I have had ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">M54.06.15</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">From Wilhelm Sonder to Diederich von Schlechtendal</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">MS not seen; text given here is extracted from Tkach, Neubauer &amp; Roser (2022), Brief 22.</seg>
                  </p>
                  <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
               </note>Hamburg d. 15 Juni 54<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">Geehrtester Herr!<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ich übersende Ihnen hiermit für die Linnaea das Manuskript der von Prof. Meisner Bearbeiteten Müller’schen Pflanzen. Ich habe mancherlei hinzufügen müssen, wodurch das Manuskript etwas bunt geworden ist. Wollen Sie gefälligst mit den Atherospermeen anfangen lassen, dann folgen die Thymeleen u.s.w. Lieb wäre es mir, wenn die Standorte wieder wie sonst in eine besondere Reihe kämen, und darunter wieder die sonstigen Bemerkungen. Prof. Meisner hat alles zu dicht zusammengeschrieben, wahrscheinlich weil er glaubt, ich werde das Ganze noch kopiren lassen. Die Arten, welche er bei seinem Hiersein als richtig anerkannte waren ganz ausgelassen. Meisner schreibt: “es wäre mir lieb, wenn ich die Plantae Müllerianae noch im Prodromus citiren könnte.“ Wie er hinzufügt, beginnt der Druck der Polygoneen am Ende dieses Monats, als so grosse Eile hat es nicht.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ich sage Ihnen meine verbindlichsten Dank für die Zannichellia. Leider muss ich gestehen, dass ich immer noch nicht zu einem Resultate gekommen bin; ich habe deshalb alles was ich besitze, an Gay in Paris geschickt und ihn um Aufschluss<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>über die Z. macrostemon, die ohne Zweifel auch in Deutschland ist, gebeten. Unter den Müller’schen Pflanzen habe ich ein neues Genus, der Zannichellia nahestehend, gefunden, das ich nachdem Gay seine Bestätigung ertheilt, beschreiben u vielleicht abbilden werden. Ich werde Ihnen als Gegengabe ein Exemplar davon zustellen.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sie hatten früher die Güte mir das III u IV Heft des 25 Bandes der Linnaea zu schicken; letzteres enthält aber die Compositae nicht vollständig.Da ich<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">alle</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Abdrucke der Compositen an Müller gesendet habe, so besitze ich selbst meine Arbeit nicht ganz u möchte Sie deshalb bitten, ob Sie mir nicht<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>den Schluss<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>der Compositae aus dem Heft V. mittheilen könnten.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ich erwarte mit Spannung aus London Bericht über das Schiff, mit welchem ich die Hälfte der Abdrucke der Compositae nach Melbourne sandte; obgleich im Mai 53 von London abgegangen, hatte Müller am 29 Janr. 54 noch nichts davon gehört. Es wäre fatal, wenn es verunglückt sein sollte, denn das andere Schiff, mit welchem ich die zweite Hälfte der Abdrucke schickte, ist bei Sidney gestrandet, wobei alles zugrunde gegangen ist.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Müllers Brief ist aus dem Inneren von Lake Omeo datiert, nachdem er nicht ohne Gefahr die alpinen Gipfel der Bogong range, die noch niemand erklommen, überstiegen. Von dort wollte er nach Gippsland, um die Gegend am Mitchell river zu besuchen und Mount Wellington zu erklettern. Er hatte im Gebirge wieder viele Pflanzen gesammelt die auf Van Diemensland<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>vorkommen. Im April wollte er wieder in Melbourne<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>sein, so dass<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>ich, wenn alles glücklich abgemacht, bald wieder einen Brief erwarten kann.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Nächstens werde ich wieder eine Parthie Manuskript senden, Hampe u. C. Müller haben die Moose der letzten Reise, die viele Interessantes u Neues enthalten, bestimmt. Ich bin mit den Algen zum grössten Theile fertig u will die gleich hinzufügen. Dann werde ich Ihnen auch die 5 Thaler für die mexikanischen Pflanzen mitsenden; ich habe augenblicklich kein Papiergeld im Hause.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">Ihr</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; text-indent: 0.493in; "
               xml:lang="de">hochachtungsvoll ergebener</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>W. Sonder</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Hamburg,15<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>June<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>1854</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Most<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>esteemed<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Sir,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am sending you herewith the manuscript of the Mueller plants worked on by Professor Meisner for the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Linnaea</seg>. I have had to add a number of things, which has made the manuscript somewhat chequered. Would you kindly start with the Atherospermataceae, followed by the Thymelaeceae<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and so on. I would appreciate it if the locations were placed in a special row as usual, with the other remarks<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>again<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>below. Professor<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Meisner has written everything too densely, probably because he thinks I will have the whole thing copied. The species that he recognised as correct when he was here were completely omitted. Meisner writes: "I would appreciate it if I<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>could still cite the Plantae Muellerianae in the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Prodromus</seg>”. As he adds, the printing of the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Polygonaceae<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>will begin at the end of this month, so there is no great hurry.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I thank you most sincerely for the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Zannichellia</seg>. Unfortunately, I must confess that I have still not come to a result.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I have therefore sent all<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I possess to Gay in Paris and asked him for information about the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Z. macrostemon</seg>, which is without<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>doubt also in Germany. Among Mueller's plants I have found a new genus, close to<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Zannichellia</seg>, which I will describe and perhaps illustrate after Gay has given his confirmation. I will send you a specimen<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of it as a return gift.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Previously you were kind<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>enough to send me<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>parts<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>III and IV<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of the 25th volume of the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Linnaea</seg>;<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the latter, however, does not contain the Compositae in their entirety. Since I have sent<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">all</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>reprints of the Compositae to Mueller, I do not possess my work in its entirety myself and would therefore like to ask you whether you could not send me the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>conclusion<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of the Compositae from<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>part<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>V.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">I am eagerly awaiting a report from London about the ship with which I sent half of the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">reprints</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of the Compositae to Melbourne</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">. A</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">lthough it left London in May 53, Müller had<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">still<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">not<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">heard anything of</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>it on 29 Jan</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">uar</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>54. It would be fatal i</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">f it should have been wrecked because</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the other ship, with which I sent the second half of the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">re</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">prints, ran aground near Sidney where everything<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">was lost</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Mue</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">ller's letter is dated from the interior<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">from</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Lake Omeo, having ascended, not without danger, the alpine peaks of the Bogong range, which no</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">-</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">one ha</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">d yet scaled. From there he intend</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">ed to go to Gippsland to visit the Mitchell<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">R</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">iver area and climb Mount Wellington. He had<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">again<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">collected many plants in the mountains that are found<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">i</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">n Van Diemen</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">'</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">s</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>La</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">nd. In April he<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">intended</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to be back in Melbourne</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>again</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">, so</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>that</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>if everything<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">succeeds well</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">, I can expect another letter soon.</seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference"
                    style="font-size: 8pt; background-color: #FFFF00; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">Letter probably sent December 1854, see 54-12-16</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">a</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">. M to WJH</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">, also <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>addressed from Omeo</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">.</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Also letter to Haines same date.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Next I will send another<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>part<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>manuscript, Hampe and C. Müller have identified the mosses of the last journey, which contain many interesting and new things. I have finished most of the algae and want to add them right away. Then I will also send you the 5 Thaler for the Mexican plants; I have no paper money<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>in the house<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>at the moment.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Your<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>respectfully<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>devoted</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>W. Sonder</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
      </body>
